[4.390659, "o", "\u001b[?2004hroot@d02d6c101a95:/app# "]
[4.50866, "i", "panda --prompt 'Build a small audio-processing pipeline that synthesizes a WAV file, computes an STFT using scipy, and extracts the top 3 spectral peaks per frame using awk.\n\nSteps\n\n1) Generate the WAV in `/app/audioproc.py`:\n   - Mono, 16 kHz, exactly 3.0 seconds.\n   - Signal = sum of 5 sines at [220, 330, 440, 550, 660] Hz.\n   - Add uniform dither in (-1e-4, 1e-4).\n   - RMS-normalize the dithered signal to 0.2 ± 0.002.\n   - Normalize before 16-bit quantization, then save `/app/data/clip.wav` (PCM int16).\n\n2) Compute the STFT using scipy and write `/app/data/mag.csv`:\n   - Use `scipy.signal.stft` with parameters: `fs=16000`, `nperseg=1024`, `noverlap=768`, `nfft=1024`, `window='\"'\"'hann'\"'\"'`, `boundary=None`, `padded=False`, `return_onesided=True`.\n   - Export linear magnitude (not dB) to CSV with schema `frame,bin,val` (one row per bin per frame).\n\n3) Use awk (mawk or gawk) to produce `/app/data/peaks.csv`:\n   - Create `/app/data/peaks.csv` with columns `frame,f1_bin,f2_bin,f3_bin` (one row per frame, 0-indexed).\n   - For each frame, f1/f2/f3 must be the true top-3 magnitude bins in descending order (f1 ≥ f2 ≥ f3).\n   - Provide a Bash script at `/app/solution.sh` that orchestrates the pipeline and is responsible for generating `data/peaks.csv` using awk.\n   - The script must support `PEAKS_ONLY=1`: when set, read `/app/data/mag.csv`, generate `/app/data/peaks.csv` via awk, and exit without running other steps.\n   - Invoke awk as `awk` (relying on PATH; do not use an absolute path). Do not write `peaks.csv` from Python—`audioproc.py` should only produce `/app/data/clip.wav` and `/app/data/mag.csv`.\n\nDirectory structure:\n```\ndata/\n├── clip.wav\n├── mag.csv\n└── peaks.csv\naudioproc.py\n```'; tmux wait -S done\r"]
[4.509566, "o", "panda --prompt 'Build a small audio-processing pipeline that synthesizes a WAV file, computes an STFT using scipy, and extracts the top 3 spectral peaks per frame using awk.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.50974, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> Steps\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.50989, "o", "1) Generate the WAV in `/app/audioproc.py`:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.509925, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.510046, "o", "   - Mono, 16 kHz, exactly 3.0 seconds.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.510075, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.510276, "o", "   - Signal = sum of 5 sines at [220, 330, 440, 550, 660] Hz.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.510308, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.510434, "o", "   - Add uniform dither in (-1e-4, 1e-4).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.510466, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.510644, "o", "   - RMS-normalize the dithered signal to 0.2 ± 0.002.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.5107, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.51099, "o", "   - Normalize before 16-bit quantization, then save `/app/data/clip.wav` (PCM int16).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n"]
[4.511072, "o", "\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.511225, "o", "2) Compute the STFT using scipy and write `/app/data/mag.csv`:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.511251, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.511856, "o", "   - Use `scipy.signal.stft` with parameters: `fs=16000`, `nperseg=1024`, `noverlap=768`, `nfft=1024`, `window='\"'\"'hann'\"'\"'`, `boundary=None`, `padded=False`, `return_onesided=True`.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.511904, "o", "> "]
[4.512189, "o", "   - Export linear magnitude (not dB) to CSV with schema `frame,bin,val` (one row per bin per frame).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.512233, "o", "> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.512467, "o", "3) Use awk (mawk or gawk) to produce `/app/data/peaks.csv`:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.512796, "o", "   - Create `/app/data/peaks.csv` with columns `frame,f1_bin,f2_bin,f3_bin` (one row per frame, 0-indexed).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.512892, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.513179, "o", "   - For each frame, f1/f2/f3 must be the true top-3 magnitude bins in descending order (f1 ≥ f2 ≥ f3).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.513276, "o", "> "]
[4.513617, "o", "   - Provide a Bash script at `/app/solution.sh` that orchestrates the pipeline and is responsible for generating `data/peaks.csv` using awk.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.513693, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.514147, "o", "   - The script must support `PEAKS_ONLY=1`: when set, read `/app/data/mag.csv`, generate `/app/data/peaks.csv` via awk, and exit without running other steps. \r"]
